&gt; 
&gt; Also, a voice may take on a different tone depending on how it is being transmitted.
&gt; 
&gt; People also like to make statements about the color a spirit may appear in. Those assessment though are made in human ignorance. For instance, if a ghost appears black, out of the baggage we humans have attached to that color, we automatically assign and evil label to it. But that isn&#39;t a proper assumption. It is our own inability to remain objective. We see a color and we get an instant motor response. Those responses are human in nature and imposed upon us by other&#39;s beliefs or other environmental factors.
&gt; 
&gt; Bottom line is when it comes to this stuff, you cannot assess anything based on beliefs. &quot;Just the facts maam...&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; You have to got by the spirits actions to tell what their demeanor is. Even then, a spirit&#39;s action can be misunderstood. Say a spirit has just thrown an object in your direction. We may automatically think of that as an aggressive attack. But the spirit is probably just trying to get your attention in the most obvious way possible. It didn&#39;t throw the thing at you to hurt you.
&gt; 
&gt; See what I&#39;m saying? The only way you can really tell a spirits demeanor is by studying that same entity for a period of time to see what the nature of its actions are.
